<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/13456569-kash-gajjar"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1349635623i/13456569._UY100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/13456569-kash-gajjar">Kash Gajjar</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Very much so. I actually found it quite factual and objectively narrated. Yes, the writers have an affection for Mountbatten and that comes through. B<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Very much so. I actually found it quite factual and objectively narrated. Yes, the writers have an affection for Mountbatten and that comes through. But they have captured the times and the events thereof perfectly, in my opinion. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
